President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key administration posts. James Q. Crowe, currently the CEO of Level 3 Communications, will be appointed as Chairman of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. Maggie Wilderotter, Chairman and CEO of Frontier Communications, will be appointed as Vice Chair of the same committee. Lastly, Donna A. James, the managing director of Lardon & Associates LLC, will be appointed as Chairperson of the National Women's Business Council. These individuals bring a wealth of experience and talent to their new roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them in the future.